00:07.500 --> 00:12.930
be able to see the cones of light in the scene as they're shining through.

00:12.930 --> 00:17.670
So I've got this light up here shining down to the ceiling.

00:17.670 --> 00:24.870
If I go over to the rendered viewport shading and let that render for a minute we can see that we've

00:24.870 --> 00:27.130
got the light coming down through the ceiling.

00:27.270 --> 00:33.900
We can see the light down here on the floor and we've got a bit of bounce light happening in the room

00:33.900 --> 00:41.970
too but we can't see that cone of light and I'd really like to have that here in the scene so to do

00:41.970 --> 00:44.890
that we need to turn on volumetric lighting.

00:44.980 --> 00:53.460
I'm going to come over here to the world panel and under here I want to go to surface now yours may

00:53.460 --> 00:58.110
say use nodes and if it does go ahead and click on that.

