02:08.100 --> 02:10.110
that we're trying to go for.

02:10.200 --> 02:18.690
So now it's a matter of adjusting your settings to the way you want it so you can maybe adjust the color

02:18.690 --> 02:21.490
of the background up a bit.

02:21.600 --> 02:27.890
You could take the density of this from point 0 1 maybe to point to.

02:27.960 --> 02:32.500
You could then bring up the ambient occlusion from point 0 to two.

02:32.520 --> 02:32.820
I don't know.

02:32.820 --> 02:36.060
Point five something like that.

02:36.180 --> 02:39.370
And it's kind of a balancing act.

02:39.390 --> 02:45.400
In addition you could go in and increase the intensity of the light itself.

02:45.750 --> 02:52.280
So there's a lot of ways you can do this but ultimately we want some balance of these settings.

02:52.380 --> 02:57.840
That gives us that volume of light coming down through the ceiling.

02:57.870 --> 03:03.510
I'll go ahead and try and increase the strength of the light here I'm going to go ahead and turn this

03:03.600 --> 03:05.280
